Evaluation of the accuracy of transvaginal sonography for the assessment of retained products of conception after spontaneous abortion. Transvaginal sonography (TVS) was used to assess uterine contents in 100 consecutive subjects presenting with a diagnosis of spontaneous abortion. TVS assessments were correlated with findings at subsequent evacuation of retained products of conception (ERPC). There was a strong correlation between the weight of the surgical specimen at ERPC with both the sagittal (r = 0.76 p < 0.05) and transverse (r = 0.73